# Adverse Event Classification

A machine learning pipeline for **pharmacovigilance adverse-event classification** using clinical narrative text plus structured patient/case features.

This project trains a classifier to identify likely serious adverse cases, generates explainability outputs, monitors drift, and scores new batches of incoming records.

---

## Project Overview

This repository contains an end-to-end workflow that:

- Trains a text + structured-data classifier on labeled pharmacovigilance cases
- Optimizes for high sensitivity to serious events (reduce missed serious cases)
- Produces model evaluation artifacts (confusion matrix, PR curve, etc.)
- Generates SHAP explainability outputs
- Runs batch scoring on new records
- Tracks experiments with MLflow

Main orchestration entrypoint:

- `run_all.py` → runs training + batch scoring and writes artifacts to `./reports/`

